## Severity
Major

## Dimension
Error Orchestration / Functional Correctness

## Location
src/tools/cron.rs:46-55 (ScheduleStore::save)

## Violation
```rust
fn save(&self) -> Result<(), String> {
    let path = PathBuf::from(SCHEDULES_FILE);
    if let Some(parent) = path.parent() {
        std::fs::create_dir_all(parent).map_err(...)?;
    }
    let json = serde_json::to_string_pretty(self).map_err(...)?;
    std::fs::write(&path, json).map_err(|e| format!("Failed to write: {e}"))
}
```

`std::fs::write` is not atomic — it truncates then writes. A process kill, OOM, or filesystem-full mid-write leaves schedules.json half-empty, which load() will then silently overwrite with Default on next start (line 39: `.unwrap_or_default()`). Every schedule the user created is permanently lost. The CompletionLedger non-atomic save problem already has issue #741 filed — same root cause class here.

## Mandated refactor
1. Write to `{SCHEDULES_FILE}.tmp` first, fsync the tmp file, then `rename` it over the target. `rename` is atomic on POSIX filesystems within the same directory.
2. Reuse a helper if one exists in the codebase; otherwise add `src/util/atomic_write.rs` and call it from both ScheduleStore and CompletionLedger (cross-reference issue #741).

